						<summary>

						<p>On the same pillar in the same place.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, in late characters, is dated Plavaṅga, Tai 5, and records the sale of a <hi rend="italic">maṟukāl</hi> (sluice) to Nayiṉār Tiruppālaivāśal Mudaliyār by the residents of Śāḻi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tiruchchamaṇamaḻagiya-nallūr, one of the villages irrigated (by the river) Tēṉāṟu.</p>						

						</summary>
